rComments: Pretty simple teacher.  Usually just goes over lecture notes which she posts online so you really don't even need to go.  If you get the study guides and just make up a list of the terms/essay questions and look for details in the book, primary sourcebook, or on Wikipedia, you can do well in this class without attending lecture.  Go to discussion.
Spends too much time on minor details and rushes important concepts that she only gets to at the last 10 minutes of the lecture.
Crowston was an OK teacher.  If you went to lecture then you could usually get away with skipping the reading.  One thing I really liked is that she posted good study guides before a test.
